ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: A discussion course, where class participation and presentations are each 25% of the grade (the other 50% is the midterm and final). We had some interesting conversations and learned some interesting things, but it wasn't like any other computer science class I've taken. I'd recommend it if you're interested in the topic of copyright law and privacy, but be warned that there's not actually a lot of computer science going on.

narratives.question_text: How did this course deepen your knowledge of your discipline/profession? To what extent did this course contribute to your dissertation/research?
comments: I learned a lot of topics related to computer science, like copyright law, privacy policy, and online identity. I would say it broadened my knowledge rather than deepened it.
Yes, the privacy related content in this course is helpful to my current social network research area.
